# <%= current_page.data.title %>

## Introduction

A suite of security alarms are configured in the [modernisation-platform-secure-baselines](https://github.com/ministryofjustice/modernisation-platform-terraform-baselines/blob/main/modules/securityhub-alarms/main.tf) module which are recommended as part of the [CIS AWS Foundations Benchmark v1.2.0](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/securityhub/latest/userguide/cis-aws-foundations-benchmark.html#cis1v2-standard).

We have adapted these slightly for our purposes, for instance we have tweaked some of the metric filter patterns to ignore changes made by knwon automation roles and we've also created new alarms for extra use cases such as monitoring use of the `AdministratorAccess` SSO role.

All of these CloudWatch alarms are configured to hit various SNS topics which in turn send to PagerDuty HTTPS service endpoints and raise incidents. These PagerDuty services are associated with a number of different Slack Channels.

